00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:19,600
- In the sense that I'm going to marry her.
- Well, she never mentioned that.

247
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:21,900
Of course she didn't.
I haven't asked her yet.

248
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,100
Wha...?

249
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:30,200
Here, sir.

250
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:33,300
What, are you two
working together now? Lupo.

251
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,100
San Cremori at dawn.

252
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:37,700
Listen. We decline to fight you, dear sir.

253
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:40,600
- You coward.
- We happen to be on good behavior.

254
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:43,700
You have no right to decline
to defend your honor.

255
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,500
It's our honor, so we have the right.

256
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:48,300
He who gets slapped has his rights.
Those are the rules.

257
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,000
See?

258
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:55,400
- Now, what did we do that for?
- I don't know.

259
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,100
San Cremori at dawn.

260
00:20:58,200 --> 00:21:00,400
May I know of whom
I have the honor to be killing?

261
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:03,000
Lupo Salvato.

262
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:05,000
Thank you.

263
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:08,200
- Don't forget your glove.
- Thank you.

264
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,200
Surely we don't mean...

265
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:14,300
What's this "we"?
You slapped him. You fight him.

266
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,800
I see you're not laughing now.

267
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,500
Come on!

268
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:54,000
The apple is very distracting.

269
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:57,100
It's all right. I'll fight him.

270
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:59,600
I can be Lupo Salvato.

271
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:03,500
Bastard!

272
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:13,300
Signor Salvato.

273
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,300
Oh, dear.

274
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:23,400
This gentleman is here to explain
the terms of the duel and to see fair play.

275
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:26,300
- Very good.
- Your attention, please, gentlemen.

276
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:29,700
Stay behind the line until I give the word.

277
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:35,000
If one trips or falls, the other puts up
his sword until I say "continue".

278
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:36,200
Yes.

279
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:40,000
If a sword breaks,
your second hands you the spare sword.

280
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,400
- Do we have a spare sword?
- Yeah, we do.

281
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:45,400
First blood ends the duel.

282
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,400
Master!

283
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,800
Move. Go on.

284
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,700
Master!

285
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,600
It's the old switch game.

286
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,500
You'd have killed him.

287
00:24:08,700 --> 00:24:11,000
And you are?

288
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:14,600
Francesca Bruni.
He's my brother.

289
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:19,100
- I'll take that, sir.
- Sorry, Signor Salvato.

290
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:21,900
I should think you would be sorry.

291
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:26,200
- It was all a case of mistaken identity.
- Mistaken identity?

292
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:30,200
Giovanni got it into his head
you were courting Signorina Donato.

293
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,300
- Did he?
- It's all over Venice.

294
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:36,300
The famously virginal Victoria Donato is
gonna marry the infamous rake, Casanova.

295
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,400
- Do you know him?
- Casanova. The philosopher,

296
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:42,900
who devotes his life to the perfection
of experience? Yes, I know him.

297
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:46,300
No. Casanova the libertine
who devotes his life to seducing women.

298
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:50,600
Well, we're obviously
talking about the same person.

299
00:24:50,900 --> 00:24:54,200
There must be something deeply wrong
with a man like that, don't you think?

300
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:58,300
Something missing in his life.
True love, perhaps.

301
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:01,300
All love is true in different ways.

302
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:06,400
To say "I love falsely" is as self-
contradictory as saying "I believe falsely".

303
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,100
You are a philosopher, too.

304
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:13,900
I've spent countless hours
alone with Casanova,

305
00:25:14,100 --> 00:25:18,200
pondering the ways of love and
how it makes us at one with the angels.

306
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:19,700
And with the beasts.

307
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:22,400
I will not debate with you
if you take the side of a man

308
00:25:22,700 --> 00:25:26,200
whose idea of love
demands a female sacrifice every day.

309
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:32,000
I've no sympathy for women who think no
better of themselves than to be a plaything.

310
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:39,000
You tell your friend from me that what
he imagines being love is, in fact, self-love.

311
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:42,000
And self-love is self-doubt.

312
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,800
- Well said.
- Yes.

313
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:47,300
By the philosopher Bernardo Guardi.
You should read him, Signor Salvato.

314
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:50,100
- Clearly.
- Give me a man who is man enough

315
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:53,800
to give himself just to the woman
who is worth him.

316
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:58,400
If that woman were me,
I would love him alone and forever.

317
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:20,800
Goodbye, Signor Salvato.

318
00:26:21,100 --> 00:26:25,300
If fighting continued, one of us
would have had good cause to be sorry.

319
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:28,700
The one still standing, I think.

320
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:38,600
Francesca Bruni.

321
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:41,000
- I want my money!
- Next week, without fail.

322
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:43,400
- You said that last week!
- I was a week early.

323
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:46,400
- Go to hell.
- I'll see you there. Thank you so much.

324
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:50,300
Honestly. Why, the nerve!

325
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:53,600
Can you believe this man?
I mean

326
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:57,000
does he know who we are?

327
00:26:58,300 --> 00:27:01,300
He should be honored
to be owed money by the likes of us.

328
00:27:01,500 --> 00:27:04,400
- Lupo.
- What?

329
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:08,200
I've made a terrible mistake.

330
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,500
- You have?
- Yes.

331
00:27:12,700 --> 00:27:14,600
I have to find her.

332
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:28,300
Master, I'm a little confused.

333
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:31,200
- I thought we'd made our decision.
- Yes, I know.

334
00:27:36,100 --> 00:27:39,200
Francesca!
He's arriving tomorrow.

335
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:41,500
Your fiance.

336
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,400
She has a fiance.

337
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:47,900
Well, so do you.

338
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:51,300
- Giovanni.
- Good day, Mario. How are you?

339
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:57,000
- I'm sorry.
- Giovanni, more disgrace.

340
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,500
- Allow me.
- Thank you. I'm sorry.

341
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:05,600
Mama, this is Signor Salvato.

342
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:11,200
I understand you've had an unpleasant
encounter with my son this morning.

343
00:28:11,500 --> 00:28:16,000
It was nothing more strenuous
than a morning's constitutional.

344
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:19,300
Come along.

345
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,600
Sorry.

346
00:28:22,700 --> 00:28:25,600
- Your sister has a fiance?
- She's in love with Casanova.

347
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:28,000
- Who is?
- Victoria.

348
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:29,700
- My love. Remember?
- Oh, yes.

349
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:32,700
- Engaged to Casanova.
- Yes.

350
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:35,400
Well, you'll have to beat him
at his own game.

351
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:39,200
But how? I'm up against
a world-class seducer.

352
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:42,600
- Hello.
- So? What would Casanova do?

353
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:49,100
- I don't know. What would Casanova do?
- Well, to start, he wouldn't mope around.

354
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:51,700
- No, I suppose not.
- Misery is not attractive.

355
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:54,400
If you want to be loved,
you have to be worth loving.

356
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:58,200
That's the first rule.
And second

357
00:28:58,500 --> 00:29:01,400
be the flame, not the moth.

358
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:05,300
- The flame, not the moth.
- Yes.

359
00:29:05,500 --> 00:29:07,800
It's my tongue.
Got very loud.

360
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:12,200
So, your sister, is she happy
with this new fiance of hers?

361
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:14,500
No. She's never met him.

362
00:29:14,700 --> 00:29:17,800
- Really?
- Besides, she has a secret lover.

363
00:29:21,300 --> 00:29:23,800
- A secret lover?
- Yeah.

364
00:29:25,500 --> 00:29:28,500
- Who?
- Well, I don't know. It's a secret.

365
00:29:29,700 --> 00:29:33,000
Anyway, she's always
sneaking off in the... See?

366
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:35,100
I'm sorry.

367
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,900
Lupo, there she is.

368
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:04,500
Casanova.

369
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:07,900
We are buying Victoria's trousseau.

370
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:12,700
Only three days to go before the wedding.

371
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:18,500
Casanova.

372
00:30:18,700 --> 00:30:23,200
No intercourse before the wedding.
I'm a traditionalist.

373
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:27,400
I mean social intercourse, of course.

374
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:30,400
Paolo. Paolo, let us off.

375
00:30:52,300 --> 00:30:53,800
A secret lover.

376
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:59,600
He's going to bang her to pieces.

377
00:31:04,700 --> 00:31:06,400
From Rome.

378
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:09,100
The Inquisitor's office.

379
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:12,500
"A cesspit of heresy and fornication. "

380
00:31:12,700 --> 00:31:15,400
Surely not...
Oh, they mean us.

381
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:21,800
127 complaints against Signor Casanova.
Do we know him?

382
00:31:22,100 --> 00:31:27,300
You'll see there are suspicions Casanova
enjoys the protection of this very office.

383
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:29,300
That's absolutely rid...

384
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:39,100
It's either his neck or it's ours.

385
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:44,000
It better be his.
Get me my notebook.

386
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:16,400
Oh, dear.

387
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:28,800
She's completely worn him out.

388
00:32:36,400 --> 00:32:38,300
I found his name.

389
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,700
He's a writer.

390
00:32:40,900 --> 00:32:44,800
"The Subjugation of Women
by Bernardo Guardi. "

391
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:49,300
No wonder. He's entered her head
and her heart as well.

392
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:53,700
"Here we live in the midst of masculine
domination and what be the result?"

393
00:32:53,900 --> 00:32:56,200
"Half the population
is missing from the feast?"

394
00:32:56,500 --> 00:33:01,300
"You have no right to property
and government, nay, not an opinion...

395
00:33:01,600 --> 00:33:05,300
"If ever a man wants to have
a woman fall in love with him,

396
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:08,800
all he need to say...

397
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:13,000
"All he need to say is,

398
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:17,300
'I have too long dominated
the conversation. What are... "'

399
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:20,600
.. your thoughts on the matter?
What are your thoughts?

400
00:33:20,900 --> 00:33:23,600
- Meat? I'm the tailor!
- So you are. Forgive me.

401
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:25,100
Thank you, sir.

402
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:28,300
What are...
What are your thoughts on the matter?

403
00:33:28,600 --> 00:33:30,900
My thoughts?
Well, I'd say...

404
00:33:31,100 --> 00:33:34,200
No, Lupo. I'm...
Could I have some tea?

405
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,600
Of course.

406
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:39,200
Mother, my fiance is turning up tomorrow.
What shall I do?

407
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:41,500
It's simple. Do your duty.

408
00:33:41,700 --> 00:33:46,100
Is it my duty to marry a man
that I don't know just because he's rich?

409
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:50,500
Yes, it is. Your duty to your father
who had your best interest at heart.

410
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:54,300
Marriage is a safe haven, my darling.

411
00:33:54,500 --> 00:33:56,700
And love?

412
00:33:56,900 --> 00:33:58,800
Love?

413
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:02,800
Love is something else.

414
00:34:04,900 --> 00:34:07,600
It's the weather being good every day,

415
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:12,400
because wind and rain
are just another kind of good weather.

416
00:34:12,700 --> 00:34:15,200
That's love.

417
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:18,200
Perhaps when you see him,
you'll fall in love with your husband.

418
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:21,200
He's not my husband yet.

419
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:25,400
If you go against your father's wishes,
we'll continue living in debt,

420
00:34:25,700 --> 00:34:28,200
at the mercy of everyone we owe.

421
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:30,900
- But if you honor the betrothal...
- The contract.

422
00:34:31,100 --> 00:34:33,600
The betrothal

423
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:36,900
then our troubles will be over.

424
00:34:41,100 --> 00:34:43,500
It's between you and your conscience.

425
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,400
Amen.

426
00:35:13,500 --> 00:35:17,300
- Signor Salvato.
- I do come here to make confession.

427
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:20,800
- What are you doing?
- What am I here to confess?

428
00:35:21,100 --> 00:35:23,800
Well, let's see.

429
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:26,500
Jealousy.

430
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:28,600
Pride.

431
00:35:30,100 --> 00:35:32,400
Covetousness.

432
00:35:32,700 --> 00:35:34,600
Despair.

433
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:38,100
And you?

434
00:35:40,700 --> 00:35:44,000
I came to prepare my soul for marriage.

435
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,400
You're troubled, Signorina Bruni.

436
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:59,600
My troubles are nothing to you, signor,
and little enough to me.

437
00:35:59,900 --> 00:36:01,700
To be bartered in marriage
is no small thing,

438
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:04,300
especially for a woman
of independent mind.

439
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:09,000
I see my brother's tongue wags again.
In future he can fight his own duels.

440
00:36:09,300 --> 00:36:12,000
- You can't come in.
- It's all right. I'm a doctor.

441
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:13,600
You're not Casanova?

442
00:36:13,700 --> 00:36:16,100
No. I can prove it
if you'll show me your chest.

443
00:36:16,300 --> 00:36:19,400
- Are you often in church?
- I followed you.

444
00:36:20,700 --> 00:36:24,200
Surely it is your friend Casanova
for whom fiancées add spice to the pursuit.

445
00:36:24,500 --> 00:36:26,900
If you knew him,
you wouldn't be so quick to condemn him.

446
00:36:27,100 --> 00:36:30,200
If you understood women,
you would not be so quick to defend him.

447
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:34,600
Love is not an affair of a night or a fortnight.

448
00:36:34,900 --> 00:36:39,400
And true love doesn't grow
with the number of lovers. It wastes away.

449
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:42,300
- Where's your instrument?
- I'll get it out in a minute.

450
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:45,500
But you can't blame those
who seek love wherever they can.

451
00:36:45,700 --> 00:36:50,800
Perhaps it's merely the murmur of the flesh
that hasn't known the flutter of the heart,

452
00:36:51,200 --> 00:36:53,900
meant for an evening but not a lifetime.

453
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:57,300
But can't that still be love all the same?

454
00:36:57,500 --> 00:37:00,100
It seems you're trying
to woo me, Signor Salvato,

455
00:37:00,300 --> 00:37:02,600
by offering to make me
a notch on your bedpost.

456
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:06,900
Come now, we are speaking of Casanova,
and I am a different man.

457
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:10,600
You see, Casanova couldn't understand

458
00:37:10,900 --> 00:37:14,300
that of all the ways love can be true, there...

459
00:37:14,500 --> 00:37:16,800
there is one way.

460
00:37:18,500 --> 00:37:23,200
And that way is the sum of all the others.

461
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:38,300
Now, I've too long
dominated the conversation.

462
00:37:38,500 --> 00:37:41,300
What are your thoughts on the matter?

463
00:37:44,100 --> 00:37:46,800
- What did you just say?
- What?

464
00:38:05,900 --> 00:38:08,400
- I'm in hell.
- I'm busy.

465
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:12,000
Another note to your lover?
I'd tell him it's all over if I was you.

466
00:38:12,300 --> 00:38:14,700
Go away.
I'm marrying Papprizzio.

467
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,900
- What did I do?
- Somebody came here

468
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:22,600
who wanted to read your latest pamphlet
before publication.

469
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:24,600
- What?
- Did you show someone my work?

470
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:29,200
I didn't show anyone anything, on the
memory of your father, whom I served well.

471
00:38:29,500 --> 00:38:31,300
Until he fired you for stealing.

472
00:38:31,900 --> 00:38:35,300
- Where's the manuscript?
- I took it to the printer's like I always do.

473
00:38:35,500 --> 00:38:38,500
You write, I get it printed under my name,
I take the commission.

474
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:42,200
Everyone's happy except the priests.

475
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:45,800
- These new shoes, Guardi?
- Church gave them to me. They don't fit.

476
00:38:46,100 --> 00:38:47,400
Don't lie.

477
00:38:47,500 --> 00:38:50,300
This is an addition to page five.
Take it to the printer's.

478
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:54,700
Nobody came. Nobody bribed me.
Would I be sober if they had?

479
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:03,300
That's him.

480
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:22,900
- Here. Add this to chapter one.
- Thank you.

481
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:43,600
Guardi says, "Why should women lace
themselves out of their natural shape?"

482
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:46,300
- Casanova.
- Signorina.

483
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:49,100
I left my window open.

484
00:39:49,300 --> 00:39:52,800
My darling, I have so many windows
and so little time.

485
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:56,700
Burn our corsets.

486
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:17,400
- What are you doing?
- Sorry. Forgive me. It was an involuntary...

487
00:40:17,700 --> 00:40:19,300
Please let me help you.

488
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:23,000
"In the heart of every woman,
there is room for a pet. "

489
00:40:23,300 --> 00:40:25,800
"Dogs and cats provide
solace and affection. "

490
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:30,000
"How rare is the man who knows
that the pet of choice for today's woman

491
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:34,900
is the intelligent and noble pig!"

492
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:40,500
- A pig?
- I'll pay for the damage. I'm well-endowed.

493
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:43,800
If you get my... I'm sorry.
That came out wrong.

494
00:40:57,500 --> 00:41:01,200
Will you tell your lady
that Signor Salvato is here with a gift?

495
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:04,700
My mistress says the pig cannot come in.

496
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:08,400
But the animal we'll take.

497
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:46,200
I have news about the fiance.
His name is Papprizzio.

498
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:49,400
He's from Genoa.
He's arriving at noon.

499
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:51,300
He's rich.

500
00:41:53,100 --> 00:41:54,400
Of course he is.

501
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:59,900
Everything's turning
against us these days, Lupo.

502
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:08,300
- How much do we owe?
- About 1500 lira.

503
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:15,300
Lay out our second-best suit, Lupo.

504
00:42:46,500 --> 00:42:48,400
Who owns this tub?

505
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:51,200
I do, sir.

506
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:54,200
And I'm Pietro Papprizzio,
merchant of Genoa.

507
00:42:54,500 --> 00:42:57,100
- And what's your cargo?
- Lard.

508
00:42:57,300 --> 00:42:59,300
- Lard?
- Finest in the world.

509
00:42:59,500 --> 00:43:02,400
- Tell him, Fulvio. Tell him.
- Yes, sir.

510
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:04,300
Tub of lard.

511
00:43:04,500 --> 00:43:08,200
Do you mean to tell me you've never
heard of my lard? We'll have to fix that.

512
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:14,400
I want to see one of these posters on every
canal, street, water corner by morning.

513
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:16,500
- Understand?
- Sign here.

514
00:43:20,900 --> 00:43:22,600
Signor Papprizzio?

515
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:26,500
- At your service, sir.
- On the contrary, I'm at yours.

516
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:31,000
The family of your fiancée sent me here to
greet you and to send you to your palazzo.

517
00:43:31,300 --> 00:43:34,700
But palazzo?
I have a reservation at the Hotel Grifasi.

518
00:43:34,900 --> 00:43:37,300
They didn't tell you?
The Grifasi is closed.

519
00:43:37,500 --> 00:43:39,300
- Really? Why?
- Lupo.

520
00:43:39,500 --> 00:43:41,500
- Rising damp, sir.
- Rising damp, indeed.

521
00:43:41,700 --> 00:43:45,200
Palazzo, eh?
Well, lead on.

522
00:43:46,500 --> 00:43:52,300
- My servant shall see to your baggage.
- I think you have everything under control.

523
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:01,400
The first thing I'm going to do

524
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:04,500
is call upon my betrothed

525
00:44:04,700 --> 00:44:07,900
after I make myself presentable, of course.

526
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:10,800
Yes. And how long does that usually take?

527
00:44:11,900 --> 00:44:14,500
"Casanova bought a pig. "

528
00:44:14,700 --> 00:44:18,200
"Casanova took the pig
to the Bruni house. "

529
00:44:21,100 --> 00:44:23,500
Clear it. Everything.

530
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:35,500
I'll take that.

531
00:44:39,100 --> 00:44:41,000
Your Grace.

532
00:44:59,400 --> 00:45:03,900
Inquisitore Dalfonso,
I am Bishop Pucci.

533
00:45:04,200 --> 00:45:06,400
Oh, Bishop...

534
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:10,000
I have been instructed to relieve you
of your duties here in Venice.

535
00:45:10,200 --> 00:45:13,300
To say that the pope is less than happy
with your rate of progress

536
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:16,300
is an understatement
of monumental proportions.

537
00:45:16,500 --> 00:45:18,900
You and your entire staff

538
00:45:19,100 --> 00:45:23,500
have been reassigned
to open a mission among the natives of

539
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:29,800
the equatorial region.

540
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:32,400
What kind of natives?

541
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:38,200
Let us just say, shall we,
they have a great hunger for religion.

542
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:50,500
So this place belonged
to the libertine Casanova, eh?

543
00:45:50,800 --> 00:45:54,900
Yes, but he ran out on his debts, so

544
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:58,100
we got the villa at a very reasonable price.

545
00:45:58,300 --> 00:46:00,400
Really? How reasonable?

546
00:46:00,600 --> 00:46:01,800
Lupo?

547
00:46:01,900 --> 00:46:04,000
- 1,600 lira.
- Yes.

548
00:46:06,700 --> 00:46:09,000
- Get a receipt.
- Of course.

549
00:46:11,100 --> 00:46:15,000
Do I get a bath for my 1,600 lira?

550
00:46:15,300 --> 00:46:19,300
"Casanova bought a pig?"

551
00:46:19,600 --> 00:46:23,500
"Casanova took pig to Bruni house. "

552
00:46:23,700 --> 00:46:27,300
"Casanova met with Papprizzio
at dockside. "

553
00:46:27,600 --> 00:46:31,100
"Took Papprizzio to his house. "

554
00:46:32,600 --> 00:46:36,300
Is there anybody here
who can explain this?

555
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:40,100
You sent them all away to be eaten.

556
00:46:40,300 --> 00:46:44,100
Well, then we shall have to do
some footwork ourselves.

557
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:48,300
Papprizzio?
The pork fat mogul from Genoa?

558
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:55,100
We're here to discover
heresy and criminal licentiousness.

559
00:46:55,300 --> 00:46:58,700
If there's bacon involved,
I dread to imagine the depths of depravity

560
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:01,400
we're going to find here in Venice.

561
00:47:01,700 --> 00:47:05,300
I'm surprised,
but I have a good feeling about this city.

562
00:47:05,500 --> 00:47:08,400
- Do you?
- There's a massive market for lard here,

563
00:47:08,700 --> 00:47:13,200
and I plan to use a good old bit
of Genoan know-how to penetrate it.

564
00:47:13,500 --> 00:47:16,600
- Good thinking.
- Handbills, newspapers.

565
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:21,100
- That's just what Venice is missing.
- That's exactly what I was thinking.

566
00:47:21,400 --> 00:47:25,500
- You have to keep an eye for that servant.
- What? He's gone out.

567
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:29,500
- He's gone out where?
- How am I supposed to know?

568
00:47:30,600 --> 00:47:37,000
I've arranged a trinket for my beloved -
a little wedding present for my bride-to-be.

569
00:47:37,300 --> 00:47:39,300
Would you like
an advanced demonstration?

570
00:47:39,500 --> 00:47:41,000
Yes, please.

571
00:47:47,500 --> 00:47:50,000
- It's very...
- That's wonderful. Exquisite.

572
00:47:50,200 --> 00:47:52,900
Really. Yeah.

573
00:47:53,100 --> 00:47:55,000
Who is it?

574
00:48:17,100 --> 00:48:19,200
Was that him?

575
00:48:19,800 --> 00:48:22,900
How am I supposed to know that?

576
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:30,100
What are we looking for?

577
00:48:30,600 --> 00:48:33,300
I don't know.
Something. Anything.

578
00:48:45,300 --> 00:48:48,300
I found the house, sir.
Signora Bruni and her daughter

579
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:52,500
request the pleasure
of your company for tea.

580
00:48:52,700 --> 00:48:54,600
Good. Good.

581
00:48:54,800 --> 00:48:58,300
The chartreuse then, I think, Fulvio.

582
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:00,400
Right away, Master.

583
00:49:02,500 --> 00:49:07,400
I'm certainly looking forward to seeing her.

584
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:09,900
Hope that she's

585
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:11,900
not disappointed by me.

586
00:49:12,800 --> 00:49:15,700
Hope that she doesn't think I'm...
I don't know.

587
00:49:15,900 --> 00:49:19,900
What's the... What's the word?
The expression I'm looking for?

588
00:49:20,200 --> 00:49:23,700
- Rotund?
- Excuse me. What did you say?

589
00:49:23,900 --> 00:49:27,300
Would sir require
a small snack before tea?

590
00:49:28,900 --> 00:49:33,500
Well, do you see that trunk
shaped vaguely like a salami?

591
00:49:33,800 --> 00:49:36,900
- Yes.
- It's filled with salami.

592
00:49:46,300 --> 00:49:48,200
- There you are.
- Yes.

593
00:49:48,400 --> 00:49:51,600
- Now, very impressive.
- Thank you.

594
00:49:51,900 --> 00:49:55,200
- The choice of lime is very slimming.
- You're too kind.

595
00:49:55,400 --> 00:49:57,700
I must be off.
Didn't I have an appointment?

596
00:49:57,900 --> 00:49:59,400
What? Oh. The publisher.

597
00:49:59,600 --> 00:50:01,400
That was it.
To see how my new book is doing.

598
00:50:01,600 --> 00:50:02,800
You're a writer.

599
00:50:02,900 --> 00:50:05,100
- I've been known to scribble a bit.
- Bravo.

600
00:50:05,300 --> 00:50:08,700
My master's a famous writer
of love and how to please ladies.

601
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:10,700
You've heard of Bernardo Guardi...

602
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:13,000
- Lupo, hush.
- But he's a friend.

603
00:50:13,200 --> 00:50:14,800
- I'm so sorry.
- Bernardo Guardi?

604
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:18,300
- I can't believe it.
- I'm so sorry. I didn't mean to.

605
00:50:18,600 --> 00:50:21,400
You, sir, are Bernardo Guardi?

606
00:50:21,800 --> 00:50:25,700
That's my nom de plume.
But you must swear to tell no one.

607
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:28,400
I swear.
On my honor, sir.

608
00:50:29,500 --> 00:50:33,600
My solemn vow.
Bernardo Guardi.

609
00:50:35,200 --> 00:50:38,800
Fulvio, this will need some thinking about.

610
00:50:39,100 --> 00:50:41,800
Yes, it does.
It's my great honor, sir.

611
00:50:44,500 --> 00:50:46,700
Look at me.

612
00:50:48,300 --> 00:50:49,400
I am.

613
00:50:51,200 --> 00:50:52,700
Now look at that.

614
00:50:57,700 --> 00:51:00,300
Yes, in truth, it is not an exact likeness, no.

615
00:51:00,500 --> 00:51:04,100
Yeah. In Genoa, we call it advertising.

616
00:51:04,300 --> 00:51:08,100
Yes. Fine. But so what of it?
If she loves you as you are...

617
00:51:08,900 --> 00:51:11,100
She's never seen me.

618
00:51:13,400 --> 00:51:14,900
- Not even a glimpse.
- Really?

619
00:51:15,100 --> 00:51:19,700
Yes. Oh, dear, Master Guardi.
Take me under your tutelage, I beg you.

620
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:23,500
I'll pay you handsomely.
Whatever you like, I'll pay it.

621
00:51:23,700 --> 00:51:25,100
You want me to tutor you?

622
00:51:25,300 --> 00:51:28,900
I want you to transform me.
Transform me.

623
00:51:29,100 --> 00:51:32,200
My dear man, but you have but an hour
until you must you meet her.

624
00:51:32,500 --> 00:51:34,900
I don't want to go.
You can't make me go.

625
00:51:37,000 --> 00:51:40,300
As it happens,
my new book, which isn't out yet,

626
00:51:40,500 --> 00:51:42,300
deals with the outer man.

627
00:51:44,000 --> 00:51:49,300
You see, the relation between the physical
and the spiritual is little understood.

628
00:51:51,500 --> 00:51:53,500
Except by me, of course.

629
00:51:57,300 --> 00:51:58,800
- Master Guardi.
- Yes?

630
00:51:59,000 --> 00:52:01,400
Can you make me look like that?

631
00:52:03,600 --> 00:52:05,200
- Yes, I can.
- Oh, God.

632
00:52:05,300 --> 00:52:07,600
But it will take courage.
It will take time.

633
00:52:07,800 --> 00:52:10,600
- Long confinement to this villa.
- Courage. Yes.

634
00:52:10,900 --> 00:52:13,400
- Do you understand?
- I understand.

635
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:17,300
Fulvio. I will send my servant Fulvio
to the house of Bruni with a note.

636
00:52:17,500 --> 00:52:20,600
- No need. I will pass that way myself.
- Oh, excellent.

637
00:52:20,900 --> 00:52:23,300
Can we start? I want to start right now.

638
00:52:23,500 --> 00:52:24,500
Lupo.

639
00:52:27,500 --> 00:52:29,500
Lovely.

640
00:52:33,600 --> 00:52:37,700
Giovanni! Signor Papprizzio
is expected at any moment.

641
00:52:44,200 --> 00:52:45,900
Signor Salvato.

642
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:55,400
Vittorio, tell Signor Salvato
I am not at home.

643
00:52:56,900 --> 00:52:59,700
Now, how strange.
I'm sure that I was invited to tea.

644
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:03,200
- You were?
- We're not having tea.

645
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:06,200
Forgive me.
I must have forgotten an invitation.

646
00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:11,300
- You told my servant, I believe.
- We were expecting Francesca's fiance.

647
00:53:11,600 --> 00:53:13,400
Indeed. And here he is.

648
00:53:15,900 --> 00:53:19,800
Ladies, forgive me. It is time I presented
myself under my true colours.

649
00:53:20,500 --> 00:53:22,700
Signorina Bruni,
my name is not Salvato.

650
00:53:22,900 --> 00:53:27,600
You see before you
your most devoted and fortunate fiance,

651
00:53:27,900 --> 00:53:31,700
Pietro Papprizzio,
all the way from Genoa.

652
00:53:32,700 --> 00:53:34,500
Signor Papprizzio.

653
00:53:37,600 --> 00:53:42,700
All the young women I met back in Genoa
concealed their true natures from me,

654
00:53:43,000 --> 00:53:46,300
dazzled by dreams of an empire of pork.

655
00:53:47,900 --> 00:53:50,300
They looked at me
and they saw a mountain of lard.

656
00:53:50,500 --> 00:53:52,200
No, no, no. Not at all.

657
00:53:52,400 --> 00:53:55,200
If anything, you need fattening up.

658
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:58,300
I don't like thin men.
Francesca's father was enormous.

659
00:53:58,600 --> 00:54:02,900
Nevertheless, I remained true
to the fiancée that I'd never seen.

660
00:54:03,800 --> 00:54:08,600
But I wanted to make sure before I declared
myself she likewise had kept herself for me

661
00:54:08,900 --> 00:54:12,200
and hadn't been seduced by the first
charmer that came along with a...

662
00:54:12,400 --> 00:54:13,800
Pig.

663
00:54:16,400 --> 00:54:21,200
Perhaps you are the charmer
you warned me against, signor.

664
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:25,100
I'm engaged to be married,
and so far all I know about you is...

665
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:28,400
Perhaps you remember sending me this.

666
00:54:30,500 --> 00:54:34,200
"To Pietro Papprizzio
from Francesca Bruni,

667
00:54:34,400 --> 00:54:37,000
with my hopes. "

668
00:54:40,700 --> 00:54:45,200
Perhaps I should've brought
the other letters you wrote me.

669
00:55:01,400 --> 00:55:04,500
The only desire I have
is that you'll come to love me.

670
00:55:04,800 --> 00:55:11,000
And if you cannot or if there is someone
else for whom your heart beats in secret,

671
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:15,200
I shall release you from your engagement.

672
00:55:15,400 --> 00:55:17,700
There isn't! There isn't.

673
00:55:17,900 --> 00:55:19,400
His Eminence, Bishop Pucci.

674
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:31,500
- Perhaps I've come at a bad time.
- No. No, Your Excellency. We're delighted.

675
00:55:31,900 --> 00:55:35,000
I should have sent word,
but since I've just arrived in Venice

676
00:55:35,200 --> 00:55:39,900
and as your husband, the late ambassador,
was so regarded by the Holy See,

677
00:55:40,200 --> 00:55:42,300
the pope was anxious to be remembered.

678
00:55:44,500 --> 00:55:48,000
Allow me to introduce
my son-in-law-to-be Signor Papprizzio.

679
00:55:49,600 --> 00:55:53,000
- Signor Papprizzio.
- Bishop.

680
00:55:53,300 --> 00:55:55,800
- My daughter Francesca.
- My dear.

681
00:55:56,000 --> 00:55:59,400
What is the pope's most feared inquisitor
doing in Venice, Bishop Pucci?

682
00:55:59,600 --> 00:56:00,500
Francesca...

683
00:56:00,700 --> 00:56:04,300
No, no. I'm delighted
that my reputation precedes me.

684
00:56:04,500 --> 00:56:07,000
The Vatican sent me
to deal with moral problems.

685
00:56:07,200 --> 00:56:12,200
- What kind of moral problems, Bishop?
- The usual. Fornication, heresy.

686
00:56:12,600 --> 00:56:15,500
How exactly does
the Church define heresy?

687
00:56:15,700 --> 00:56:17,800
Francesca!

688
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:21,200
I hardly think heresy
is a fit conversation for a young lady.

689
00:56:21,400 --> 00:56:24,200
Why? Can't we be heretics?

690
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:29,400
I think my fiancée, Bishop Pucci,
wishes to learn more from you perhaps.

691
00:56:30,300 --> 00:56:32,000
If you please.

692
00:56:32,500 --> 00:56:34,400
Very well.

693
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:39,200
Heresy is an affront
to the teachings of the Church.

694
00:56:39,500 --> 00:56:43,200
It is a rebellion against
our mores and our morals.

695
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:47,000
More to the point,
and you will understand this,

696
00:56:47,300 --> 00:56:50,500
since you are a woman
and understand women's ways,

697
00:56:50,700 --> 00:56:53,700
hence the concept of "whim",

698
00:56:54,600 --> 00:56:58,300
heresy is whatever I say it is.

699
00:57:01,700 --> 00:57:05,400
For example, that writer fellow,
Bernardo Guardi, he is a heretic.

700
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:07,200
And why is that?

701
00:57:08,400 --> 00:57:10,700
Vittorio, where is the tea?

702
00:57:10,900 --> 00:57:14,600
Guardi's words
cause women to feel dissatisfied

703
00:57:14,900 --> 00:57:17,600
- and men to doubt their manhood.
- Really?

704
00:57:17,800 --> 00:57:22,500
If you are an admirer of this Guardi fellow,
I have some very sad news for you.

705
00:57:22,800 --> 00:57:24,300
He's written out.

706
00:57:26,200 --> 00:57:29,400
My colleagues are scouring
the streets for him as we speak.

707
00:57:34,300 --> 00:57:35,400
I'm so sorry.

708
00:57:35,600 --> 00:57:40,100
- Bishop, will you take tea?
- Thank you, no. I have people to see.

709
00:57:43,900 --> 00:57:46,300
Signorina Bruni.

710
00:57:46,500 --> 00:57:50,900
May I have the honor
of accompanying you to the carnival ball?

711
00:57:58,000 --> 00:58:00,300
But I've done nothing wrong.

712
00:58:02,800 --> 00:58:05,800
I'm innocent!
You've got the wrong man! Let me go!

713
00:58:06,300 --> 00:58:08,200
Come on. Come on.

714
00:58:15,000 --> 00:58:17,700
I have an urgent message for you
from Bernardo Guardi.

715
00:58:17,900 --> 00:58:19,400
Who are you?

716
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:23,800
Never mind. The Chief Inquisitor from
Rome is here and he is out for blood.

717
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:27,400
- Delay publishing the new pamphlet.
- You're a little late.

718
00:58:27,700 --> 00:58:29,800
Oh, my God. Stop selling it.

719
00:58:30,000 --> 00:58:32,800
- Sorry.
- That's what it says. The pig.

720
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:36,500
- Well, I've always owned pigs.
- Oh, tit.

721
00:58:51,200 --> 00:58:52,300
Right.

722
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:56,700
Now, make sure it's ready
in time for the ball.

723
00:58:56,900 --> 00:58:58,400
Ah. Master.

724
00:58:58,600 --> 00:59:02,000
- How's the treatment going?
- Well...

725
00:59:02,100 --> 00:59:04,400
- Is he any better?
- Yeah, well...

726
00:59:04,600 --> 00:59:07,500
It's impossible he could look any worse.

727
00:59:07,700 --> 00:59:11,300
Is that you, Maestro?
Maestro Guardi, is that you?

728
00:59:11,600 --> 00:59:15,400
- Hello. Who's there?
- Good God. You achieved the impossible.

729
00:59:15,700 --> 00:59:18,100
- Thank you.
- What have you smeared all over him?

730
00:59:18,300 --> 00:59:21,400
- Lard, mostly. Mint jelly.
- Hello?

731
00:59:21,500 --> 00:59:24,400
- A few coffee grounds.
