and he's under my protection.

927
01:14:43,300 --> 01:14:46,400
Does your protection extend to heretics?

928
01:14:46,600 --> 01:14:49,900
Beware, Doge.
Your city's freedom

929
01:14:50,200 --> 01:14:53,800
dangles from the belt of the Vatican.

930
01:14:58,200 --> 01:15:00,100
You're welcome.

931
01:15:22,300 --> 01:15:26,800
- Admiral Massimo Canal and Signora.
- You're welcome.

932
01:15:27,100 --> 01:15:28,500
Where's Francesca?

933
01:15:28,600 --> 01:15:32,300
My name is Pietro Papprizzio
and I'm from Genoa.

934
01:15:33,100 --> 01:15:35,000
What?

935
01:15:38,100 --> 01:15:41,000
Signor Papprizzio of Genoa.

936
01:16:21,300 --> 01:16:23,600
So you're Papprizzio?

937
01:16:26,200 --> 01:16:28,900
From Genoa?

938
01:16:32,100 --> 01:16:33,400
Is your name...

939
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:35,300
Bruni.

940
01:16:37,700 --> 01:16:39,800
I'm your...

941
01:16:39,800 --> 01:16:41,000
I'm your future...

942
01:16:41,100 --> 01:16:43,900
I never dreamt you'd be so beautiful.

943
01:16:44,100 --> 01:16:45,900
Me?

944
01:16:50,600 --> 01:16:52,900
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

945
01:16:53,100 --> 01:16:54,100
Why...

946
01:16:54,200 --> 01:16:58,100
No. No, I'm your future mother-in-law.

947
01:16:58,400 --> 01:17:00,900
- My mother-in-law?
- Yes.

948
01:17:01,100 --> 01:17:04,900
- I'm not betrothed to you?
- No, to my daughter.

949
01:17:07,100 --> 01:17:09,900
Some people find her beautiful.

950
01:17:10,100 --> 01:17:14,300
- There's a man who's after her.
- Really? Does she like him?

951
01:17:14,600 --> 01:17:18,100
Signora Bruni, your daughter has been
duped by none other than Casanova.

952
01:17:18,300 --> 01:17:20,200
But worry not. He's as good as...

953
01:17:24,100 --> 01:17:29,600
Why don't you stop interfering, all right?

954
01:17:31,300 --> 01:17:33,200
Thank you.

955
01:17:35,100 --> 01:17:36,500
Well.

956
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:53,400
Signorina.

957
01:17:53,600 --> 01:17:56,100
I was afraid I'd lost you.

958
01:17:56,200 --> 01:17:58,800
As one might lose a pocket watch,
Signor Papprizzio,

959
01:17:59,000 --> 01:18:02,000
or some other valuable possession?

960
01:18:02,200 --> 01:18:04,800
I know that no man will ever own you.

961
01:18:05,000 --> 01:18:08,200
But to be your defender
on the road you travel,

962
01:18:08,500 --> 01:18:14,300
to show you the world as you've
never seen it, for that I hold my hopes.

963
01:18:14,500 --> 01:18:18,200
Let's start by taking
one step closer to heaven.

964
01:18:56,000 --> 01:18:58,200
You get this one here.

965
01:18:58,400 --> 01:19:00,300
Ready. On the count of three.

966
01:19:00,400 --> 01:19:02,500
One, two, three.

967
01:19:25,400 --> 01:19:26,700
Witchcraft.

968
01:19:30,500 --> 01:19:35,600
Actually, I believe it's because hot air rises,
overcoming the gravitational force of...

969
01:19:35,900 --> 01:19:38,100
Witchcraft.

970
01:19:48,100 --> 01:19:50,000
Here we are.

971
01:19:53,100 --> 01:19:56,200
Look! It's Casanova with his new fiancée.

972
01:20:04,700 --> 01:20:07,700
Casanova.

973
01:20:08,000 --> 01:20:09,700
Come on.

974
01:20:09,800 --> 01:20:12,700
Is that Francesca?

975
01:20:13,000 --> 01:20:15,900
- It is her.
- That's Francesca.

976
01:20:16,100 --> 01:20:19,600
- I've never seen her look so happy.
- Really?

977
01:20:21,200 --> 01:20:25,200
Such bad news for you, Signor Papprizzio.

978
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:32,800
O calamity.
She's thrown me over.

979
01:20:33,000 --> 01:20:37,100
- Disgraceful.
- Oh, well. A scandal.

980
01:20:40,200 --> 01:20:43,900
- You're a free man.
- Oh, dear.

981
01:20:45,900 --> 01:20:48,000
What will I do?

982
01:21:07,100 --> 01:21:10,400
Thank you, Signor Papprizzio.

983
01:21:12,000 --> 01:21:15,700
I'm beginning to believe
that your heart is true.

984
01:21:16,700 --> 01:21:20,600
There is more of the lover
than the merchant in you.

985
01:21:20,900 --> 01:21:23,900
Why didn't you tell me
you were my betrothed?

986
01:21:24,100 --> 01:21:26,400
You didn't trust me?

987
01:21:27,600 --> 01:21:31,800
Well, why didn't you tell me
you were Bernardo Guardi?

988
01:21:36,700 --> 01:21:39,700
It's all right.
I won't tell anyone.

989
01:21:41,800 --> 01:21:48,000
I should've guessed the first time I saw you
in that citadel of male complacency

990
01:21:48,400 --> 01:21:52,900
when you were as brave in debate
as you were later in duel.

991
01:21:57,400 --> 01:22:00,600
You were Bernardo Guardi
in beauty's mask.

992
01:22:03,900 --> 01:22:06,300
I'm in love with you, Francesca.

993
01:22:12,900 --> 01:22:14,500
You were at the debate?

994
01:22:17,000 --> 01:22:18,900
Yes. Yes, I was.

995
01:22:19,000 --> 01:22:21,100
At the university.

996
01:22:23,700 --> 01:22:26,300
Francesca...

997
01:22:28,300 --> 01:22:33,200
Just as you had honest reason
for not telling me who you were,

998
01:22:35,000 --> 01:22:39,700
I, too, have honest reason...

999
01:22:41,000 --> 01:22:42,400
What?

1000
01:22:54,000 --> 01:22:55,200
I can explain this.

1001
01:22:56,400 --> 01:22:58,500
Are you Papprizzio?

1002
01:23:00,200 --> 01:23:04,200
Tell me you're Papprizzio, my betrothed.

1003
01:23:07,200 --> 01:23:09,100
Who are you?

1004
01:23:15,000 --> 01:23:16,900
I'm Casanova.

1005
01:23:17,700 --> 01:23:19,700
What?

1006
01:23:19,800 --> 01:23:23,600
I'm... I'm Giacomo Casanova.

1007
01:23:27,100 --> 01:23:30,000
You stand for everything I write against.

1008
01:23:32,300 --> 01:23:36,000
- Wasn't that before you knew me?
- I don't know you.

1009
01:23:36,800 --> 01:23:38,900
Which one of you?

1010
01:23:50,100 --> 01:23:54,900
I think I liked you better in your masks.
At least Salvato was a gentleman.

1011
01:23:55,200 --> 01:23:59,100
Papprizzio was promising.
But Casanova, I despise.

1012
01:23:59,400 --> 01:24:01,100
You dare to say you love me.

1013
01:24:01,200 --> 01:24:06,600
I would save myself for the kind of love
which a man would give his life for.

1014
01:24:18,000 --> 01:24:19,500
- Are you hurt?
- I'm fine.

1015
01:24:19,700 --> 01:24:22,100
Casanova.

1016
01:24:23,200 --> 01:24:25,000
Signor Casanova.

1017
01:24:25,200 --> 01:24:28,900
I'm here to arrest you
as a fornicator, a charlatan,

1018
01:24:29,200 --> 01:24:34,000
and, above all, a coward
who hides behind the name of another -

1019
01:24:34,300 --> 01:24:37,000
Signor Bernardo Guardi.

1020
01:24:40,700 --> 01:24:44,300
And as Bernardo Guardi,
I arrest you as a heretic.

1021
01:24:44,600 --> 01:24:48,400
- What? He's not...
- Yes, signorina, he is.

1022
01:24:48,700 --> 01:24:51,900
- He's not...
- Francesca, don't.

1023
01:24:53,600 --> 01:24:56,100
No.

1024
01:24:59,400 --> 01:25:01,500
I'm Bernardo Guardi.

1025
01:25:32,600 --> 01:25:34,900
Bishop Pucci.

1026
01:25:35,000 --> 01:25:37,800
How can I help you, my dear?

1027
01:26:05,300 --> 01:26:06,900
I was a virgin.

1028
01:26:07,100 --> 01:26:11,500
My virginity was
my most cherished possession -

1029
01:26:11,800 --> 01:26:13,900
my gift from God.

1030
01:26:14,900 --> 01:26:17,400
My gift was taken from me.

1031
01:26:17,600 --> 01:26:21,700
Tragic and most damnable.
What was the name of this vile seducer?

1032
01:26:22,700 --> 01:26:24,100
Giacomo Casanova.

1033
01:26:26,700 --> 01:26:31,300
When Casanova came to my room
and robbed me

1034
01:26:33,200 --> 01:26:35,600
I fought for my honor.

1035
01:26:35,800 --> 01:26:40,100
Are you saying you'd be willing to give me
the testimony that I need to hang him?

1036
01:26:40,400 --> 01:26:42,000
Yes.

1037
01:26:42,100 --> 01:26:45,100
But I would worry about my reputation.

1038
01:26:45,400 --> 01:26:50,100
Of course. But I think we could say
if everything went according to plan,

1039
01:26:50,300 --> 01:26:54,700
we could return your reputation
and your virginity to you.

1040
01:26:55,900 --> 01:26:58,100
- You could do that?
- Oh, yes.

1041
01:26:58,300 --> 01:27:01,200
We are the Catholic Church.
We can do anything.

1042
01:27:13,200 --> 01:27:17,100
Excuse me.
When is my turn?

1043
01:27:21,200 --> 01:27:23,100
Give me a man who is man enough

1044
01:27:23,300 --> 01:27:27,000
to give himself
just to the woman who is worth him.

1045
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:30,600
And if that woman were me,

1046
01:27:30,800 --> 01:27:34,900
I would love him alone and forever.

1047
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:27,900
Thank you very much.

1048
01:28:28,100 --> 01:28:31,300
- Are you sure I don't owe you anything?
- On the contrary.

1049
01:28:31,400 --> 01:28:33,000
- Thank you.
- Bye.

1050
01:28:33,100 --> 01:28:36,700
- Bye.
- Come back.

1051
01:28:36,900 --> 01:28:39,800
You're... You're the boy in the window.

1052
01:28:40,800 --> 01:28:42,200
Signorina Donato.

1053
01:28:42,300 --> 01:28:44,400
We won't forget you.

1054
01:28:44,600 --> 01:28:47,900
You'll be a legend among the girls.

1055
01:28:50,000 --> 01:28:53,300
- This is terrible.
- Why?

1056
01:28:56,000 --> 01:28:58,200
I've loved you hopelessly for years.

1057
01:29:00,400 --> 01:29:03,300
Why didn't you say?

1058
01:29:18,500 --> 01:29:23,600
My Lord, the prisoner is being represented
by a Dr Giordano of Padua.

1059
01:29:25,600 --> 01:29:28,800
Then I call the defense, Dr Giordano.

1060
01:29:30,000 --> 01:29:32,600
It is a case of mistaken identity,
Your Grace.

1061
01:29:32,800 --> 01:29:34,600
- What? Mistaken...
- Yes.

1062
01:29:34,800 --> 01:29:39,000
This man is not Bernardo Guardi.

1063
01:29:39,300 --> 01:29:41,000
- Yes, he is.
- Yes, I am.

1064
01:29:41,100 --> 01:29:43,800
- You see?
- He is protecting someone.

1065
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:45,500
- No.
- Yes, you are.

1066
01:29:45,600 --> 01:29:48,700
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are... not.

1067
01:29:49,400 --> 01:29:51,100
Protecting who?

1068
01:29:53,600 --> 01:29:55,400
The woman who loves him.

1069
01:30:01,100 --> 01:30:04,500
If you are who you say, perhaps you could
indulge the court with a few samples

1070
01:30:04,700 --> 01:30:07,400
of your more renowned
philosophies on women.

1071
01:30:10,900 --> 01:30:14,100
If I've said I am Bernardo Guardi,
does that not suffice?

1072
01:30:14,200 --> 01:30:18,700
My Lord, must we listen to this
stuttering heretic? He has self-confessed.

1073
01:30:19,000 --> 01:30:22,300
Is that all that you require?
A confession?

1074
01:30:22,600 --> 01:30:25,200
Well, yes. I suppose so.

1075
01:30:26,200 --> 01:30:28,900
Good.

1076
01:30:31,100 --> 01:30:36,300
Because I am the one with
the manuscripts, written in my own hand.

1077
01:30:36,600 --> 01:30:38,900
I am the only one with proof that I...

1078
01:30:39,900 --> 01:30:42,900
I am Bernardo Guardi.

1079
01:30:43,600 --> 01:30:45,400
You?

1080
01:30:45,500 --> 01:30:48,400
- Francesca.
- Do you really think I'd let you die for me?

1081
01:30:48,600 --> 01:30:51,400
Well, then, release the prisoner Casanova.

1082
01:30:51,600 --> 01:30:56,900
My Lord, my Lord,
let us not forget this is a court of law.

1083
01:30:57,300 --> 01:31:00,200
We still have a self-confessed heretic.

1084
01:31:00,300 --> 01:31:04,500
And we also have
a notorious seducer,

1085
01:31:04,800 --> 01:31:08,100
an adulterer, a violator of virgins

1086
01:31:08,300 --> 01:31:11,400
whose guilt I will prove
by the testimony of...

1087
01:31:11,600 --> 01:31:13,200
No!

1088
01:31:13,300 --> 01:31:15,200
It wasn't true.

1089
01:31:18,000 --> 01:31:19,200
Of...

1090
01:31:19,400 --> 01:31:24,600
By the testimony of no less
than 127 sworn statements,

1091
01:31:24,900 --> 01:31:29,000
attesting to the libidinous lust
of Giacomo Casanova.

1092
01:31:30,200 --> 01:31:33,900
There is only one verdict
open to this court: guilty.

1093
01:31:34,600 --> 01:31:38,300
And one sentence: death.

1094
01:31:38,900 --> 01:31:42,700
- Death to the heretic Bernardo Guardi.
- No!

1095
01:31:42,800 --> 01:31:46,600
And death to the master fornicator

1096
01:31:46,800 --> 01:31:49,400
Giacomo Casanova.

1097
01:32:45,000 --> 01:32:48,800
- You did say the cardinal's coming.
- I did, sir.

1098
01:33:13,000 --> 01:33:16,700
Your Reverence,
I don't think we can wait any longer.

1099
01:33:16,900 --> 01:33:18,900
Very well.

1100
01:33:20,000 --> 01:33:21,800
I shall have to do it without him.

1101
01:33:43,400 --> 01:33:46,500
Cardinal Lopresta has arrived!

1102
01:34:06,100 --> 01:34:08,700
Sorry we're late.
Canals, et cetera.

1103
01:34:08,900 --> 01:34:11,800
Your Eminence.
Bishop Pucci.

1104
01:34:12,100 --> 01:34:14,000
An honor to meet you at last.

1105
01:34:14,100 --> 01:34:17,300
- I've heard so much about you.
- Thank you.

1106
01:34:17,600 --> 01:34:19,800
What's happening here?

1107
01:34:20,000 --> 01:34:25,300
Just hanging a heretic and Casanova.

1108
01:34:25,600 --> 01:34:26,700
What luck.

1109
01:34:28,600 --> 01:34:31,000
My nurse.

1110
01:34:32,200 --> 01:34:35,600
And does your nurse enjoy executions?

1111
01:34:35,800 --> 01:34:38,300
Does the pope have a balcony?

1112
01:34:38,500 --> 01:34:41,000
What I actually came to say is this.

1113
01:34:45,000 --> 01:34:45,900
Venetians!

1114
01:34:47,600 --> 01:34:50,400
Greetings from His Holiness.

1115
01:34:50,600 --> 01:34:54,700
As you know,
today is the pope's birthday.

1116
01:34:55,700 --> 01:34:57,100
- And...
- Did you know that?

1117
01:34:57,300 --> 01:35:02,800
And in honor of his birthday,
His Holiness has decreed

1118
01:35:03,200 --> 01:35:08,300
a papal pardon for all those
who would be executed

1119
01:35:08,500 --> 01:35:12,000
on this happy day.

1120
01:35:12,200 --> 01:35:14,400
- Your Eminence.
- Free the prisoners.

1121
01:35:16,400 --> 01:35:18,600
Free the prisoners!

1122
01:35:23,700 --> 01:35:26,400
Your Eminence.
No. No. No.

1123
01:35:27,000 --> 01:35:30,200
You don't seem to share
the pope's happiness on his birthday.

1124
01:35:30,500 --> 01:35:32,100
No, I do. I do.

1125
01:35:34,500 --> 01:35:36,600
How old is he?

1126
01:35:36,800 --> 01:35:38,900
I'm not quite sure.

1127
01:35:43,700 --> 01:35:47,600
- No, no...
- Best stay here. Crowd's turning ugly.

1128
01:35:52,200 --> 01:35:56,900
Please join me in my coach.
We're leaving for my country house.

1129
01:36:17,000 --> 01:36:20,100
I'm so sorry I'm late.

1130
01:36:22,700 --> 01:36:25,600
My fault. I'm to blame.

1131
01:36:26,700 --> 01:36:27,900
Tito.

1132
01:36:28,000 --> 01:36:30,000
The love of my life.

1133
01:36:31,500 --> 01:36:35,300
This is my son.

1134
01:36:36,400 --> 01:36:39,600
I've played cardinals before, of course.
You may have seen me.

1135
01:36:39,800 --> 01:36:44,700
Anyway, we left our troupe in Trieste when
we heard the news. Had to move fast.

1136
01:36:47,500 --> 01:36:49,400
Mom, the paint is wet.

1137
01:36:53,300 --> 01:36:55,100
It says "Theatre Troupe" here.

1138
01:36:58,000 --> 01:37:00,800
Cardinal Lopresta has arrived!

1139
01:37:00,900 --> 01:37:02,500
Arrest those impostors!

1140
01:37:08,000 --> 01:37:10,400
Move! Get out of the way!

1141
01:37:11,600 --> 01:37:12,900
Giacomo!

1142
01:37:15,500 --> 01:37:18,800
- Come on!
- Come on! Out of the way, people!

1143
01:37:19,000 --> 01:37:20,800
Casanova!

1144
01:37:38,300 --> 01:37:40,900
On you get, darling.
Quick as a bunny.

1145
01:37:44,300 --> 01:37:46,800
I didn't know it was the pope's birthday.

1146
01:38:28,900 --> 01:38:31,300
So how goes things?

1147
01:38:33,200 --> 01:38:35,800
It's very exciting, isn't it?

1148
01:38:38,300 --> 01:38:40,800
This is the last time I'm traveling coach.

1149
01:38:41,000 --> 01:38:42,900
Hold on, everyone!

1150
01:38:49,800 --> 01:38:50,900
Hang on!

1151
01:38:56,100 --> 01:38:59,400
- Easy, boy!
- Tito!

1152
01:39:06,900 --> 01:39:09,600
Everybody off.

1153
01:39:11,200 --> 01:39:14,500
Hello, darling.
I'm your future stepfather.

1154
01:39:14,800 --> 01:39:18,900
- I was always faithful to you.
- I never had any doubt. None at all.

1155
01:39:19,100 --> 01:39:23,400
Come on, darling.
Let's escape on my barge. It's by the water.

1156
01:39:25,800 --> 01:39:27,400
That way.

1157
01:39:27,600 --> 01:39:29,700
Charge!

1158
01:39:39,100 --> 01:39:41,300
Oh, dear.

1159
01:39:43,000 --> 01:39:44,500
Giovanni!

1160
01:40:18,900 --> 01:40:21,900
Step lightly, darling.
Excuse us. Excuse us.

1161
01:40:22,100 --> 01:40:24,200
Out of the way.
Out of the way. Excuse us.

1162
01:40:24,400 --> 01:40:27,800
This way, darling.
This way.

1163
01:40:28,100 --> 01:40:32,900
I can't wait for you to see the boat. Here's
the boat. Right this way. On your new boat.

1164
01:40:33,200 --> 01:40:35,500
- Vittorio. Vittorio.
- Careful. Careful.

1165
01:40:35,700 --> 01:40:37,400
- I'm behind you.
- This way.

1166
01:40:37,600 --> 01:40:41,800
No, my baby. Listen.
You're staying behind with me.

1167
01:40:43,900 --> 01:40:46,400
Prepare to sail, men.

1168
01:40:50,100 --> 01:40:51,500
Oh, dear.

1169
01:40:54,000 --> 01:40:55,800
Vittorio, do something useful.

1170
01:40:55,900 --> 01:40:59,100
- Signora, what can I do?
- Something useful.

1171
01:41:00,000 --> 01:41:01,900
Giovanni!

1172
01:41:02,100 --> 01:41:04,000
Come on! Come on!

1173
01:41:04,000 --> 01:41:06,200
Quickly! Quickly!

1174
01:41:09,000 --> 01:41:13,200
I can't come with you.
If I do, they'll follow us both.

1175
01:41:14,000 --> 01:41:14,900
What?

1176
01:41:15,100 --> 01:41:17,700
- You mean they'll follow Casanova?
- That's right.

1177
01:41:19,200 --> 01:41:21,500
What if he never left?

1178
01:41:24,300 --> 01:41:26,200
I could do it.

1179
01:41:28,900 --> 01:41:31,100
There's more to this than just the name.

1180
01:41:33,100 --> 01:41:35,100
I wouldn't mind being Casanova.

1181
01:41:36,100 --> 01:41:41,500
- I wouldn't mind being on that boat.
- And I wouldn't mind my wedding.

1182
01:41:45,500 --> 01:41:47,800
Well, come on.

1183
01:41:48,900 --> 01:41:51,100
- Come on.
- Lupo, where you going?

1184
01:41:51,300 --> 01:41:52,900
I'm staying.

1185
01:41:53,500 --> 01:41:55,900
- Why?
- I'm a Venetian, sir.

1186
01:41:56,100 --> 01:41:58,900
My place is with Casanova.

1187
01:42:02,300 --> 01:42:04,800
Take care of me, my good friend.

1188
01:42:05,800 --> 01:42:07,200
Of course, Master.

1189
01:42:36,700 --> 01:42:38,000
After them!

1190
01:42:40,600 --> 01:42:42,300
Better luck next time!

1191
01:42:52,100 --> 01:42:56,500
- Andolini, get the boats after them!
- Farewell, simpletons!

1192
01:43:00,900 --> 01:43:02,900
Get after them!

1193
01:43:03,100 --> 01:43:05,000
Go on!

1194
01:43:20,200 --> 01:43:22,600
I told you I'd come back.

1195
01:43:36,600 --> 01:43:40,200
It's a wonderful life, an actor's life.

1196
01:43:40,400 --> 01:43:42,600
You'll love it.

1197
01:43:43,800 --> 01:43:46,900
Who writes your plays?

1198
01:43:54,300 --> 01:43:56,400
Come inside.

1199
01:44:02,700 --> 01:44:04,200
Lovely.

1200
01:44:04,300 --> 01:44:07,200
Just my kind of good weather.

1201
01:44:41,800 --> 01:44:46,500
Which is why the story
of Casanova and Francesca

1202
01:44:49,200 --> 01:44:51,400
isn't mine to tell.

1203
01:44:55,200 --> 01:45:00,800
Victoria and I lived happily ever after.

1204
01:45:04,600 --> 01:45:07,100
Just not together.

1205
01:45:10,100 --> 01:45:12,000
Venice.

1206
01:45:13,300 --> 01:45:17,100
So soon enough, in people's minds,

1207
01:45:17,300 --> 01:45:20,000
Casanova was back.

1208
01:45:21,700 --> 01:45:23,300
If I may say so,

1209
01:45:23,500 --> 01:45:26,900
I believe I rose worthily to the occasion

1210
01:45:28,400 --> 01:45:33,200
and added many glorious chapters
